  "text": "As mentioned above, the water-binding energies for the [U]Na + and [SU]Na + complexes are similar within experimental uncertainty (see Fig. 6 and Table 2 ). This likely reflects the fact that the interaction between Na + and the nucleobase in these complexes is essentially electrostatic [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and the binding strengths between the complexes and H 2 O is determined by the charge retained on Na + in [U]Na + and [SU]Na + , which is expected to decrease as the metal ion affinity (MIA) of the neutral nucleobase increases. Table 2 shows that the MIA values for uracil [CITATION_3] and thiouracils [CITATION_4] are all similar, spanning a 12 kJ/mol range. The experimentally derived MIA values are also similar within 7 kJ/mol.",
